Question

A sinusoidal wave is graphed below.


Estimate the period of the sinusoidal function graphed above.

Solution

Find the time difference between corresponding points in sequential repetitions.


\[P~=~ (0.4)-(-3.2)\] \[P = 3.6\]

This exact function could be plotted with the following algebraic definition: \[y(t) = 1.2 \sin\left(\frac{2\pi}{3.6}(t+0.5)\right)+(2)\]

The amplitude is 1.2; the period is 3.6; the horizontal shift is left by 0.5; and the midline is \(y=2\).
